SIMPLE: matted
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Matted
<hw>Mat"ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Matte</er>.]</ety> <def>Having a dull surface; lusterless;
unburnished; same as <er>matte</er>; <as>as, <ex>matted</ex> gold leaf
or gilding</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Matted glass</b></col>, <cd>glass ornamented with figures
on a dull ground.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Matted</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Matted
<hw>Mat"ted</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See 3d <er>Mat</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Covered with a mat or mats; <as>as, a <ex>matted</ex>
floor</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Tangled closely together; having its parts adhering
closely together; <as>as, <ex>matted</ex> hair</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Matter</ent>⟦br⟧
